profiles:
Summary Broad experience uniquely combining skills sets in:  

* Software System Security; 
* Computer Software Development; 
* System Design;  
* Scientific Research Strategies;  
* Project Management; 
* Technology Transfer; 
* Intellectual Property development and management;  
* Product Commercialization;  
* FDA/ISO Regulatory Compliance; and 
* Medical Device Development  

with access to a Broad Network of National Level External Scientific Research Community organizations and National Industry Associations.  

These areas are complimented with over 20 years experience in project management with responsibilities for personnel management, fiscal management, product lifecycle development, formal process implementation, testing & quality assurance, marketing, international business development/management, meeting facilitation, mentoring, training delivery, collaboration development, programming, and the ability to bridge between the technology and business worlds. 

Demonstrated ability to provide effective and secure solutions to software process, software design and development challenges for large and complex product development teams. Excellent oral and written communication skills. Ability to formulate and communicate design approaches in a succinct and effective manner to all levels of the development team and stakeholders including cross-geo teams. A Certified Ethical Hacker, a Certified Project Management Professional, and a Certified Information Systems Security Professional with fluency in English & Spanish. An advocate for strengthening Diversity in the workplace and past Cross-Site Chair for the Intel Latino Network. Specialties:Software Security, Technology Transfer, Economic Development, Embedded Software Development, General Software Development, Project Management, Certified Project Management Professional, Certified Ethical Hacker, Certified Information Systems Security Professional. 

